<p>So i decided to try and create an instant messagin application using the new bostons tutorials. I went throuh without any problems, but i recently wanted to use the sendSignal method i made from another object. I got no errors, it simply dosnt send it. Posting my "test code", below. Its not how the code is, but it shows the problem i have. </p>  <pre><code>class Client extends JFrame {      public void sendSignal(String message) {         try {             output.writeObject(message);             output.flush();             showMessage("\n" + message);         } catch (IOException ioException) {             terminal.append("\n Error: E400");         }     }      public void showMessage(final String text) {         SwingUtilities.invokeLater(                 new Runnable() {                     public void run() {                         terminal.append(text);                     }                 }         );     } }  // MAIN METHOD:  import javax.swing.JFrame ;  public class ConSetUpClass {      public static void main(String[] args) {         Client stream;         stream = new Client("127.0.0.1");         stream.setDefaultCloseOperation(JFrame.EXIT_ON_CLOSE);         stream.runClient();          stream.sendSignal("x");     } } </code></pre>  <p>This should send and show "x". But it dosnt, it dosnt even give me an error. Im greateful for all answeres!</p>